Buckingham Palace confirmed the Duke of York would not be part of the service in Windsor although he will attend the investiture and the lunch behind closed doors. It is understood the decision for Andrew, whose reputation has been severely tarnished by his involvement in a civil sex case lawsuit, not to take part publicly in Garter Day was a "family decision". The Queen will also miss the ceremony at St George's Chapel, but is expected to attend the lunch. FOLLOW BELOW FOR UPDATES... 